==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Besort
<hw>Be*sort"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To assort or be
congruous with; to fit, or become.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such men as may <qex>besort</qex> your age.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Besort</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Besort
<hw>Be*sort"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Befitting associates or
attendants.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With such accommodation and <qex>besort</qex>⟦br⟧
As levels with her breeding.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Besot</ent>⟦br⟧
